page.title: 03POOLE KEYNES - BUILDINGS
page.content: In{Poole Keynes}there are a few old buildings including my house. It has been in our family for over 200 years and my dad has kept up the farming tradition. It was built over 600 years ago. It is built of{Cotswold}stone and has a big round chimney. There is a big room in the house which was used as a coach house or a ballroom. Another old building is the church which is next door to us. The church was built in 1467. It is called "St. Michael and All Angels". It does not have a spire, just a tower like a castle. Occasionally, the Sunday School meets there. The church isn't very big but you can hear the bell a long way away. The only other buildings of interest are the old vicarage and the Queen Victoria Memorial.
